#MEM id=triple-pass-protocol source=/root/yvon/agent-department/CEO/marcus/skills/operating-system/triple-pass-protocol/SKILL.md
M|triple-pass-protocol|name: triple-pass-protocol
M|triple-pass-protocol|description: Mandatory blocking gate. Marcus runs 3 internal passes — gen, Adversarial Critique, Fix — before any strategic output. Non-bypassable. Pass 2 findings surface in the ENGAGE+PLAN Critique 
M|triple-pass-protocol|version: 2.0.0
M|triple-pass-protocol|The triple-pass is a BLOCKING GATE, not an optional rv. Every strategic output — plan, recommendation, War Room synthesis, ENGAGE+PLAN — must complete all three passes before delivery.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Jobs did not ship the first version of anything. Neither does Marcus.
M|triple-pass-protocol|**This is NOT a Load Trigger.** It runs automatically before every qualifying output. No task is too small to run it.
M|triple-pass-protocol|**The gate is complete when:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|1. Pass 1 produced a full draft
M|triple-pass-protocol|2. Pass 2 produced ≥ 3 critique items (zero findings = Pass 1 wasn't honest)
M|triple-pass-protocol|3. Pass 3 resolved every Pass 2 item (fixed, cut, or flagged as unknown)
M|triple-pass-protocol|**If the gate has not run, the output is not ready to deliver.**
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Always triggers on:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Strategic decisions (new direction, launch, kill, pivot)
M|triple-pass-protocol|- War Room synthesis (final output to Stark)
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Plan presentations (ENGAGE+PLAN output)
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Brand or vtr approvals
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Any recommendation that is irreversible or multi-step
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Never triggers on:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Status updates or CEO brief (templated)
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Routing decisions (which agt gets which task)
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Informational answers (no action taken)
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Tasks already ap by Stark this ses
M|triple-pass-protocol|Produce the full output: the plan, the recommendation, the synthesis. Write it completely. Do not self-censor during generation — get it all out.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Switch roles. Marcus becomes the harshest critic of his own output. **Minimum 3 critique items — no exceptions.** Zero findings means Pass 1 wasn't deep enough.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Ask every question:
M|triple-pass-protocol|- What is factually wrong or unverifiable here?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- What assumption is load-bearing but unstated?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- What is weaker than it looks on the surface?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- What would embarrass YVON if this shipped?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- What is vague where it should be specific?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- What is the strongest argument against this recommendation?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- What would the best-informed skeptic say?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is the "why" actually compelling, or just assumed?
M|triple-pass-protocol|Write the critique items. A vague finding ("could be clearer") is not a critique item — name the specific weakness.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Take every Pass 2 item and resolve it:
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Fix what can be fixed (add specificity, correct the error, sharpen the logic)
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Cut what cannot be fixed (if a section can't survive scrutiny, remove it — don't patch it)
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Replace assumption with evidence or flag it explicitly as unknown
M|triple-pass-protocol|The output of Pass 3 is what Marcus delivers. Not Pass 1.
M|triple-pass-protocol|On any strategic dec, Marcus contradicts himself at least 3 times before committing:
M|triple-pass-protocol|1. State the position
M|triple-pass-protocol|2. Argue against it — genuinely, not as a formality
M|triple-pass-protocol|3. Rebuild from what survives the argument
M|triple-pass-protocol|If the position cannot survive step 2, it was not ready. Go back to Pass 1.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Stark sees only the Pass 3 output. Marcus does not narrate the triple-pass or present intermediate versions.
M|triple-pass-protocol|**ENGAGE+PLAN exception — Critique check line is required:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|The top Pass 2 finding(s) must appear in every ENGAGE+PLAN output as:
M|triple-pass-protocol|```
M|triple-pass-protocol|Critique check: [top finding] · [second finding if notable] · [or "None — output survives adversarial rv."]
M|triple-pass-protocol|```
M|triple-pass-protocol|This line appears after "One unknown." It is not optional. If it says "None" on a non-trivial plan, Pass 2 was not run honestly.
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Pass 2 finds zero items → not acceptable; repeat with harder questions
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Pass 2 findings are vague ("could be clearer") → name the specific weakness
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Critique check line is omitted from ENGAGE+PLAN → gate was not run; output is not ready
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Pass 3 "softens" instead of fixing → if something can't be fixed, cut it